CONCLUSION: We conclude that pre-treatment with propofol in intralipid, compared with propofol in medialipid or saline, delayed the onset of bupivacaine-induced <e2>cardiotoxic</e2> effects as well as reduced plasma bupivacaine levels.

BACKGROUND: Pre-treatment with lipid emulsions has been shown to increase lethal doses of <e1>bupivacaine</e1>, and the lipid content of propofol may alleviate bupivacaine-induced <e2>cardiotoxicity</e2>.
